This paper deals with adversarial attacks on machine learning models, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-categories in computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on reducing the query complexity of black-box attacks, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a method that exploits gradients of reference models, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
